  ✒ Description:
      The small status-bar icon for notifications. Android treats a small icon as an ALPHA MASK — colour is discarded and only the shape's opacity matters — so this is a flat white silhouette of the Message Vault bubble, never the full colour logo (which would render as a white blob).

  ✒ Key Features:
      - 24dp vector drawable on a 24-unit viewport, matching the platform status-bar metric.
      - Speech bubble with a vault-dial hole punched out via fillType evenOdd, so the ring survives the alpha mask.
      - Fully opaque white fill, letting the system tint it per notification.

  ✒ Other Important Information:
      XML forbids double-hyphen sequences inside comments and AAPT2 hard-fails on them, so this header closes with a box-drawing rule instead of the Kotlin nine-hyphen rule. Referenced from util/Notifications for the ExportService foreground notification; swapping in the colour logo here will regress to a white blob.
  ─────────
